  "prompt": "Why was MM kalburgi killed?",
  "response": "MM Kalburgi, a well-known Kannada scholar and rationalist, was assassinated on August 30, 2015, in Dharwad, Karnataka, India. His murder was widely believed to be linked to his outspoken views on superstitions, religious practices, and certain cultural traditions. Kalburgi was critical of various religious dogmas and was known for advocating rationalism and free thinking. His critiques often targeted the practices of both Hinduism and other religions, which earned him both supporters and detractors.\n\nThe killing was part of a broader context of rising intolerance and violence against thinkers and activists in India who challenged religious orthodoxy and advocated for secularism. Kalburgi's assassination was met with widespread condemnation and raised concerns about freedom of expression and the safety of intellectuals in the country. In the aftermath, there were various protests and calls for justice, highlighting the challenges faced by those who speak out against established beliefs.",
